sp.p:
And thus became a settler and my neighbour;
thanks to the drum and fife and the white
cockade, that lured you from your home.

Come, sit down, farmer and neighbours;
and you, my pretty lads and lasses, let's have a
dance. Ah, here is a foraging party.

You shall be taken care of, dear Adela;
we will place you in the rear, among the baggage
waggons.

Not a word, dear general, not a word;
I have merely done my duty, and done no more
than every soldier in our ranks.

We have not done this, deluded man;
your pretended advocates, over the great waters,
have told you this tale.
